      • verifySendMoneyCases_insufficientWalletAmount_viaMobile

        public void verifySendMoneyCases_insufficientWalletAmount_viaMobile()
                                                             throws java.lang.Exception
        method to verify the different send money scenarios. Below are the covered scenarios for now: 1) insufficient balance - less money available in wallet then trying to transfer.(mobile/contact list/email) 2) invalid amount case - less than Rs. 5 (mobile/contact list/email) 3) empty transfer attempt - trying to send Rs. 0 (mobile/contact list/email) 4) successful attempt - money sent successfully 5) Invalid Mobile/Email 6) Sending Money to Self (Mobile/email) 7) Sending Money when logged out(mobile/contact list/email) 8) Non-existing Mobile/Email 9) A sending money B Accepting (mobile/contact list/email) 10) A sending B Declines (mobile/contact list/email) 11) A sends and cancels (mobile/contact list/email)
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception - - when any exception comes
